[Ann] <i>
Way back...</i><i>
Harder, harder...</i>

1296
01:19:12,269 --> 01:19:13,923
-Billy?
-Sherry?

1297
01:19:18,101 --> 01:19:19,450
Good morning, Bill.

1298
01:19:21,974 --> 01:19:23,454
Hey, how you doin'?

1299
01:19:27,763 --> 01:19:29,547
It's my responsibility
to inform you

1300
01:19:29,590 --> 01:19:32,942
that you are a ward of
the United States Government.

1301
01:19:33,769 --> 01:19:34,813
Yeah.

1302
01:19:35,640 --> 01:19:37,381
And to notify you
of your selection

1303
01:19:37,424 --> 01:19:39,470
for a national health project.

1304
01:19:43,822 --> 01:19:44,954
Uh-huh.

1305
01:19:48,609 --> 01:19:50,002
I have something to show you.

1306
01:19:53,136 --> 01:19:55,486
I want you to look at it
very carefully.

1307
01:20:01,971 --> 01:20:03,494
[exhales deeply]

1308
01:20:08,151 --> 01:20:11,415
"Highs in the mid
to upper 40s...

1309
01:20:11,458 --> 01:20:12,590
unseasonably mild."

1310
01:20:12,633 --> 01:20:14,548
Please note the paper's date.

1311
01:20:18,291 --> 01:20:20,511
November 16th...

1312
01:20:21,773 --> 01:20:23,383
2027.

1313
01:20:27,953 --> 01:20:29,476
Let's come at this gradually.

1314
01:20:34,351 --> 01:20:37,963
These are admittance papers
from October 22nd, 1999,

1315
01:20:38,007 --> 01:20:39,965
to the Sumner Hospital.

1316
01:20:40,009 --> 01:20:42,141
As you can see,
it includes the EMT report,

1317
01:20:42,185 --> 01:20:45,405
the attending
physician's report,
the standard admission form.

1318
01:20:46,798 --> 01:20:48,365
That's the last page.

1319
01:20:49,496 --> 01:20:51,847
-On the bottom
is your mother's signature.
-I see it.

1320
01:20:55,894 --> 01:21:00,029
[supervisor] This one
is from February 10, 2000.

1321
01:21:03,119 --> 01:21:05,991
This form authorizes your
transfer to the comatose ward.

1322
01:21:06,035 --> 01:21:09,690
Again, your mother's signature
about two-thirds of the way
down the page.

1323
01:21:10,648 --> 01:21:11,736
Right.

1324
01:21:22,878 --> 01:21:25,706
-Sherry signed this?
-[door buzzes]

1325
01:21:25,750 --> 01:21:28,013
-Excuse me, I--
-Just a moment.

1326
01:21:29,406 --> 01:21:30,755
Please listen carefully.

1327
01:21:32,452 --> 01:21:35,064
You were in a coma
for approximately
two and a half years,

1328
01:21:35,107 --> 01:21:37,893
and during that time
your mother passed away.

1329
01:21:37,936 --> 01:21:41,113
-She had named Sherry Winslow
executrix of her estates.
-Sherry Clarke.

1330
01:21:41,157 --> 01:21:44,377
The medical opinion
was that you would make
no recovery.

1331
01:21:44,421 --> 01:21:47,032
That you would remain in a coma
until your death.

1332
01:21:47,076 --> 01:21:50,470
Now, February 10, 2003...

1333
01:21:51,558 --> 01:21:54,083
Mrs. Winslow was given
the option of remanding you

1334
01:21:54,126 --> 01:21:57,782
to an experimental
cryogenics research program,
which she did.

1335
01:21:57,825 --> 01:22:00,089
-By that time, it's standard--
-Doctor.

1336
01:22:03,614 --> 01:22:05,311
Three months ago,

1337
01:22:05,355 --> 01:22:09,272
25 years after your freezing,
you were successfully revived.

1338
01:22:09,315 --> 01:22:11,274
[Ann]
There were only 11 revivals

1339
01:22:11,317 --> 01:22:14,581
out of 300 cryogens
in this country.

1340
01:22:14,625 --> 01:22:17,715
This is a consent form
for a surgical operation,

1341
01:22:17,758 --> 01:22:20,500
the dangers of which
are fully outlined.

1342
01:22:32,338 --> 01:22:34,210
-At this time--
-[Ann] Bill.

1343
01:22:34,253 --> 01:22:36,603
-Doctor.
-I'm sorry.

1344
01:22:36,647 --> 01:22:39,911
This is something
you can elect not to sign.

1345
01:22:39,955 --> 01:22:41,304
-Uh-huh.
-[man] That is correct.

1346
01:22:41,347 --> 01:22:42,914
However, we are now authorized

1347
01:22:42,958 --> 01:22:45,830
to exercise forced consent
at our discretion.

1348
01:22:45,873 --> 01:22:49,051
-Which means that it wouldn't--
-[Ann] But if you wish,
then you may--

1349
01:22:49,094 --> 01:22:51,967
-Absolutely.
-[man] Yes, if you wish.

1350
01:22:52,010 --> 01:22:53,707
Ah!

1351
01:22:53,751 --> 01:22:56,014
[quiet, tense music]

1352
01:22:56,884 --> 01:22:59,017
You've just been given
a mild sedative.

1353
01:23:00,192 --> 01:23:03,804
In approximately 25 minutes
you will be further sedated

1354
01:23:03,848 --> 01:23:06,285
in preparation
for your surgery.

1355
01:23:06,329 --> 01:23:09,810
Because of the high degree
of risk involved,

1356
01:23:09,854 --> 01:23:11,290
it's my obligation to ask you

1357
01:23:11,334 --> 01:23:14,206
if you have
a final meal preference...

1358
01:23:16,208 --> 01:23:19,168
and if you wish to be visited
by a religious proctor.

1359
01:23:23,737 --> 01:23:26,175
Please indicate your choices
on the form.

1360
01:23:34,009 --> 01:23:35,314
I want to thank you.

1361
01:23:44,367 --> 01:23:45,585
My office.

1362
01:23:48,371 --> 01:23:49,763
[door buzzes]

1363
01:23:57,858 --> 01:23:59,686
-[door closes]
-[lock beeps]

1364
01:24:08,086 --> 01:24:10,828
[Bill]
Left a few details out
yesterday, didn't you?

1365
01:24:10,871 --> 01:24:12,047
Excuse me?

1366
01:24:13,048 --> 01:24:14,266
You heard me.

1367
01:24:17,878 --> 01:24:18,966
[Ann] Yes.

1368
01:24:31,936 --> 01:24:33,024
So, what do I do?

1369
01:24:33,068 --> 01:24:34,895
What do you want to do?

1370
01:24:35,766 --> 01:24:37,550
-Do you know what to do?
-Yes.

1371
01:24:39,248 --> 01:24:41,250
You don't always
know what to do.

1372
01:24:44,731 --> 01:24:46,037
Whoa...

1373
01:24:46,081 --> 01:24:48,257
[bass guitar music]

1374
01:24:49,258 --> 01:24:52,043
[Bill imitating blues guitar]

1375
01:24:52,087 --> 01:24:54,524
Freddie King...
[sniffs]

1376
01:24:54,567 --> 01:24:56,613
...blues guitar genius.

1377
01:24:57,962 --> 01:24:59,964
White guys stole
everything he knew.

1378
01:25:02,053 --> 01:25:03,794
Millionaires, a lot of 'em...

1379
01:25:04,621 --> 01:25:06,144
Like me.

1380
01:25:09,452 --> 01:25:11,584
Those guys could play, though.
Wow.

1381
01:25:11,628 --> 01:25:13,412
[faint blues guitar playing]

1382
01:25:14,587 --> 01:25:15,806
Hmm...

1383
01:25:20,724 --> 01:25:24,119
Whew...
they could lock off your heart
and throw away the key.

1384
01:25:27,861 --> 01:25:30,081
[exhales]
Not me, though.

1385
01:25:30,125 --> 01:25:31,604
Oh!

1386
01:25:31,648 --> 01:25:32,997
Oh...

1387
01:25:36,653 --> 01:25:39,046
Okay. Come on.

1388
01:25:39,090 --> 01:25:40,091
Get up.

1389
01:25:40,135 --> 01:25:41,832
Yeah. Hmm?

1390
01:25:44,139 --> 01:25:47,838
-[intense music]
-[Ann gasping]

1391
01:25:57,369 --> 01:25:58,849
[door buzzes]

1392
01:26:03,027 --> 01:26:04,159
[lock beeps]

1393
01:26:06,465 --> 01:26:08,293
♪

1394
01:26:18,825 --> 01:26:20,871
[panting]

1395
01:26:22,177 --> 01:26:24,570
-[whimpers]
-[door buzzes]

1396
01:26:32,361 --> 01:26:34,014
[tense music]

1397
01:27:14,577 --> 01:27:17,493
[strange, animalistic
crying sound]

1398
01:27:17,536 --> 01:27:19,234
[muffled voices]

1399
01:27:27,546 --> 01:27:30,114
[blues guitar]

1400
01:27:45,085 --> 01:27:46,783
[no audible dialogue]

1401
01:28:07,282 --> 01:28:09,153
[no audible dialogue]

1402
01:28:17,422 --> 01:28:18,684
[Bill]
Sherry?

1403
01:28:21,513 --> 01:28:22,775
Sher?

1404
01:28:33,308 --> 01:28:34,483
[music fades]

1405
01:28:34,526 --> 01:28:36,615
-I'd like to administer--
-No.

1406
01:28:36,659 --> 01:28:38,617
-It's my case.
-It's my responsibility.

1407
01:28:38,661 --> 01:28:41,272
-Excuse me, Doctor.
-Not now.

1408
01:28:41,316 --> 01:28:42,926
He knows me now.

1409
01:28:42,969 --> 01:28:45,145
It will be easier for him
if I do this.

1410
01:28:45,189 --> 01:28:47,887
-Ann.
-It'll be more humane.

1411
01:28:50,629 --> 01:28:51,978
Please?

1412
01:28:55,373 --> 01:28:56,635
Please.

1413
01:29:03,294 --> 01:29:04,948
You have ten minutes,

1414
01:29:04,991 --> 01:29:06,079
then I send prep.

1415
01:29:07,994 --> 01:29:09,518
Ten minutes, Doctor.

1416
01:29:13,348 --> 01:29:14,740
I'm exhausted.

1417
01:29:24,707 --> 01:29:27,362
[muffled electric guitar solo]

1418
01:29:39,722 --> 01:29:44,117
[skillful guitar solo]

1419
01:30:39,912 --> 01:30:41,174
[solo ends]

1420
01:30:48,268 --> 01:30:49,356
[pick clatters]

1421
01:30:59,758 --> 01:31:03,762
-[crashing]
-[amplifier feedback rings]

1422
01:31:09,638 --> 01:31:11,335
[wood splintering]

1423
01:31:15,644 --> 01:31:18,037
-[clattering]
-[amplifier humming]

1424
01:31:26,437 --> 01:31:28,178
-[switch clicks]
-[humming stops]

1425
01:31:28,961 --> 01:31:30,310
[exhales audibly]

1426
01:31:35,490 --> 01:31:36,795
How 'bout that, huh?

1427
01:31:37,492 --> 01:31:38,841
[clatters]

1428
01:31:38,884 --> 01:31:41,496
Bet you never heard
anything like that before.

1429
01:31:41,539 --> 01:31:43,628
There was a lot of good players
30 years ago.

1430
01:31:43,672 --> 01:31:45,630
You missed it.
Too bad.

1431
01:31:45,674 --> 01:31:47,371
You shouldn't have broken it.

1432
01:31:47,414 --> 01:31:49,286
I'll get another one.
I'm rich.

1433
01:31:49,329 --> 01:31:50,505
I'll get another one.

1434
01:31:56,685 --> 01:31:58,382
You ever killed anybody before?

1435
01:32:01,690 --> 01:32:03,430
There's a lot
you don't know, Bill.

1436
01:32:03,474 --> 01:32:04,910
I know you're gonna kill me.

1437
01:32:07,217 --> 01:32:09,480
And you seem calm about it all.

1438
01:32:09,524 --> 01:32:11,700
-I do?
-Yeah, you do.

1439
01:32:12,396 --> 01:32:14,703
-Let me tell you something--
-I don't wanna hear any more.

1440
01:32:27,846 --> 01:32:29,587
Things can happen here, still.

1441
01:32:31,023 --> 01:32:32,895
-What things?
-[thuds]

1442
01:32:43,035 --> 01:32:44,254
[Bill]
Mom?

1443
01:32:45,385 --> 01:32:46,561
Yes, honey?

1444
01:32:47,083 --> 01:32:49,389
-Mom.
-Yes.

1445
01:32:49,433 --> 01:32:52,479
Is a pony--
Would a pony--

1446
01:32:52,523 --> 01:32:54,525
Is a pony a baby horse?

1447
01:32:54,569 --> 01:32:55,787
No.

1448
01:32:56,396 --> 01:32:58,573
What is a baby horse, then?

1449
01:32:58,616 --> 01:32:59,791
A foal.

1450
01:33:00,575 --> 01:33:01,576
A foal.

1451
01:33:02,446 --> 01:33:04,361
Now get some sleep.

1452
01:33:04,404 --> 01:33:07,320
Mom...
can we please get a foal?

1453
01:33:10,367 --> 01:33:12,587
If you go through with this,

1454
01:33:12,630 --> 01:33:14,197
it'll be underneath
everything you do

1455
01:33:14,240 --> 01:33:16,373
for the rest of your life.

1456
01:33:16,416 --> 01:33:17,983
I know that.

1457
01:33:18,767 --> 01:33:19,985
Get us out.

1458
01:33:20,899 --> 01:33:22,379
I don't wanna get out.

1459
01:33:22,422 --> 01:33:23,772
Get me out.

1460
01:33:25,382 --> 01:33:26,470
Listen.

1461
01:33:29,168 --> 01:33:31,606
Just listen, listen.

1462
01:33:32,389 --> 01:33:34,609
[soft acoustic guitar music]

1463
01:33:36,219 --> 01:33:37,612
I know a place...

1464
01:33:38,482 --> 01:33:39,614
a mesa.

1465
01:33:42,138 --> 01:33:44,923
I'll set you
on this adobe wall...

1466
01:33:44,967 --> 01:33:46,316
in the sunlight.

1467
01:33:47,709 --> 01:33:50,494
I'll be behind you
with my arms around your waist.

1468
01:33:53,105 --> 01:33:54,367
You'll hear a sound.

1469
01:33:55,847 --> 01:33:57,196
Look up.

1470
01:34:00,460 --> 01:34:03,333
Wind... in a crow's feathers.

1471
01:34:05,509 --> 01:34:07,337
That's how quiet it is.

1472
01:34:09,861 --> 01:34:12,777
-And I will never leave you--
-No, I can't.

1473
01:34:12,821 --> 01:34:14,387
Why not?

1474
01:34:16,476 --> 01:34:17,826
I have a sister.

1475
01:34:20,872 --> 01:34:22,265
Where is she?

1476
01:34:22,308 --> 01:34:23,962
Another wing.

1477
01:34:24,006 --> 01:34:26,008
-Here?
-Yes.

1478
01:34:26,051 --> 01:34:27,400
She works here?

1479
01:34:27,444 --> 01:34:29,664
No, she is a patient here.

1480
01:34:29,707 --> 01:34:30,926
Uh-huh.

1481
01:34:30,969 --> 01:34:32,101
You would like her.

1482
01:34:32,144 --> 01:34:33,363
Why?

1483
01:34:33,406 --> 01:34:35,452
I just think that you would.

1484
01:34:35,495 --> 01:34:37,019
And why is she here?

1485
01:34:40,500 --> 01:34:42,851
There is an epidemic.

1486
01:34:44,330 --> 01:34:46,855
♪

1487
01:34:46,898 --> 01:34:48,204
Like an...

1488
01:34:49,379 --> 01:34:52,861
environmental viral syndrome
times a thousand.

1489
01:34:54,558 --> 01:34:59,302
Her cell wall linings
in her blood vessels

1490
01:34:59,345 --> 01:35:03,872
are disintegrating
and the vessels are rupturing.

1491
01:35:07,092 --> 01:35:09,660
You have an immunological agent
in your body.

1492
01:35:09,704 --> 01:35:12,707
You have it because
you were frozen before--

1493
01:35:12,750 --> 01:35:15,622
you were never exposed
to this virus.

1494
01:35:15,666 --> 01:35:17,668
Well, get a needle
and take it out.

1495
01:35:17,712 --> 01:35:19,539
It's deep in the tissue

1496
01:35:19,583 --> 01:35:22,368
above the top of the spine
in the brain stem.

1497
01:35:22,412 --> 01:35:25,676
-Knock me out, cut it out.
-We can't do that.

1498
01:35:25,720 --> 01:35:27,722
This is a 15-hour operation

1499
01:35:27,765 --> 01:35:30,420
that will either kill you
or will leave you...

1500
01:35:33,423 --> 01:35:35,338
The injection
will kill you swiftly.

1501
01:35:35,381 --> 01:35:36,687
And I'm the last guy?

1502
01:35:36,731 --> 01:35:38,733
I'm the last frozen guy?

1503
01:35:38,776 --> 01:35:40,430
There are two of you here.

1504
01:35:41,953 --> 01:35:44,434
You're the only real hope
at this point.

1505
01:35:48,090 --> 01:35:50,048
I know the country
that you were describing.

1506
01:35:50,092 --> 01:35:51,920
I was a girl there.

1507
01:35:56,968 --> 01:35:58,448
It's gone.

1508
01:36:01,146 --> 01:36:04,149
There's nothing now
but this nightmare.

1509
01:36:04,193 --> 01:36:07,413
Uh, you and me and my sister...

1510
01:36:23,778 --> 01:36:26,128
♪

1511
01:37:09,345 --> 01:37:12,827
I want you to read "Birches"
by Robert Frost
at the gravesite.

1512
01:37:15,003 --> 01:37:18,049
And then I want you
to go to the beach...

1513
01:37:18,876 --> 01:37:21,531
and wait for the sky
to get very colorful...

1514
01:37:22,880 --> 01:37:26,318
and get very loaded...
and tell stories about me.

1515
01:37:27,537 --> 01:37:30,018
Heck of a guy.
So sad.

1516
01:37:30,801 --> 01:37:32,977
Seems like only yesterday.

1517
01:37:33,021 --> 01:37:34,152
Whoa.

1518
01:37:36,024 --> 01:37:37,416
Whoa.

1519
01:37:38,896 --> 01:37:43,335
You know, go over
and get that yellow thing
over there, okay?

1520
01:37:43,379 --> 01:37:45,337
-Just...
-What?

1521
01:37:45,381 --> 01:37:47,992
Under... under the...

1522
01:37:51,213 --> 01:37:54,956
That's a Walkman.
Under the bed, yeah.

1523
01:37:54,999 --> 01:37:56,566
Walk that over here.

1524
01:38:02,746 --> 01:38:05,662
-You sing?
-What?

1525
01:38:05,705 --> 01:38:07,664
-Can you sing?
-Oh.

1526
01:38:07,707 --> 01:38:09,231
There you go, good.

1527
01:38:10,885 --> 01:38:12,582
Sing along with this.

1528
01:38:15,193 --> 01:38:16,281
Hit it.

1529
01:38:18,718 --> 01:38:19,894
Go ahead.

1530
01:38:22,070 --> 01:38:23,723
Go ahead.
They won't demote you.

1531
01:38:26,378 --> 01:38:29,120
[Ann humming]

1532
01:38:30,078 --> 01:38:34,865
<i>♪ The battle cry of freedom </i>

1533
01:38:34,909 --> 01:38:38,390
<i>♪ Rally 'round the flag, boys </i>

1534
01:38:38,434 --> 01:38:41,741
<i>♪ Rally 'round the flag </i>

1535
01:38:41,785 --> 01:38:48,009
<i>♪ Sounding the battle cry</i><i>
Of freedom ♪</i>

1536
01:38:48,052 --> 01:38:49,793
No, no. No, no.

1537
01:38:56,931 --> 01:38:58,584
She's your baby sister?

1538
01:39:03,763 --> 01:39:05,243
Thanks for the song.

1539
01:39:06,766 --> 01:39:08,551
A nice song, isn't it?

1540
01:39:08,594 --> 01:39:10,205
Yes.

1541
01:39:10,248 --> 01:39:12,294
Tell her I'm sorry
we didn't get a chance to meet,

1542
01:39:12,337 --> 01:39:17,560
but I got detained up here
in the final ward,

1543
01:39:17,603 --> 01:39:22,260
but I'd like her to accept,
as a token of my affection,

1544
01:39:22,304 --> 01:39:25,916
this batch
of 100 percent pure,

1545
01:39:25,960 --> 01:39:30,442
old-style...
immunological agent.

1546
01:39:33,489 --> 01:39:36,013
And then you lean down
and you kiss her.

1547
01:39:38,146 --> 01:39:40,626
I mean really kiss her...

1548
01:39:40,670 --> 01:39:42,585
and tell her
if things were different,

1549
01:39:42,628 --> 01:39:45,240
-if this was maybe 1974--
-[electronic alarm beeps]

1550
01:39:45,283 --> 01:39:46,632
What's that?

1551
01:39:48,330 --> 01:39:49,809
